GATB-Pipeline
-------------

Installation:
-------------

    1) Prerequisites: 

        Linux 64 bits (for Minia binary)

        bwa (for BESST)
        Python >= 2.7 with the following modules (for BESST): 
            mathstats
            scipy 
            networkx 
            pysam
            
            To install all of them at once, run:
               pip install --user mathstats pysam networkx scipy pyfasta
            Can't install scipy? get activestate python: http://www.activestate.com/activepython/downloads and type 'pypm install scipy'

    2) Type `make`

usage:

     ./gatb -1 read_1.fastq -2 read_2.fastq
 or
     ./gatb --12 interleaved_reads.fastq
 or
     ./gatb -s single_reads.fastq

More input options are available. Type `./gatb` for extended usage.
Type `make test` to launch a small test.

FAQ
---

If you get the following error during the pipeline (BESST): "'NoneType' object has no attribute 'actualSolve'", then you need to type "sudo pulptest" (root required).


